### Basic Rollup Configuration with PostHog Plugin

Source: https://github.com/posthog/posthog-js/blob/main/packages/rollup-plugin/README.md

Demonstrates how to add the PostHog plugin to your Rollup configuration file. It requires essential options like `personalApiKey` and `envId`, and enables source map uploading with basic project and version details.

```javascript
import posthog from '@posthog/rollup-plugin'

export default {
    input: './src/index.ts',
    output: {
        format: 'es',
        dir: 'dist',
    },
    plugins: [
        posthog({
            personalApiKey: process.env.POSTHOG_PERSONAL_API_KEY,
            envId: process.env.POSTHOG_PROJECT_ID,
            sourcemaps: {
                enabled: true,
                project: 'my-app',
                version: '1.0.0',
            },
        }),
    ],
}
```

