### Configure PostHog Sourcemaps in Next.js

Source: https://github.com/posthog/posthog-js/blob/main/packages/nextjs-config/README.md

This snippet demonstrates how to integrate the PostHog Next.js config package into your Next.js application. It shows the necessary import and how to wrap your existing Next.js configuration with `withPostHogConfig`. This setup enables sourcemap generation and upload for PostHog Error Tracking, requiring API keys and environment IDs.

```typescript
import {
  withPostHogConfig,
} from "@posthog/nextjs-config";

const nextConfig = {
  // Your Next.js configuration here
};

export default withPostHogConfig(nextConfig, {
  personalApiKey: process.env.POSTHOG_PERSONAL_API_KEY!,
  envId: process.env.POSTHOG_ENV_ID!,
  host: process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_HOST!,
  sourcemaps: {
    enabled: true,
    project: "my-application",
    version: "1.0.0",
    deleteAfterUpload: true,
  },
});
```

