### Configure Nuxt Module for Error Tracking with Sourcemaps (TypeScript)

Source: https://context7.com/posthog/posthog-js/llms.txt

Sets up the PostHog Nuxt module to enable error tracking with line-level context via sourcemap uploads. This configuration in `nuxt.config.ts` enables client-side autocapture, pageviews, session recording, and server-side request timeouts, along with sourcemap generation and upload.

```typescript
// nuxt.config.ts
export default defineNuxtConfig({
    modules: ['@posthog/nuxt'],

    sourcemap: { client: 'hidden' },

    nitro: {
        rollupConfig: {
            output: {
                sourcemapExcludeSources: false
            }
        }
    },

    posthogConfig: {
        host: 'https://us.i.posthog.com',
        publicKey: '<ph_project_api_key>',
        clientConfig: {
            autocapture: true,
            capture_pageview: true,
            session_recording: {
                maskAllInputs: true
            }
        },
        serverConfig: {
            requestTimeout: 10000
        },
        sourceMaps: {
            enabled: true,
            envId: '2',
            project: 'my-nuxt-app',
            version: '1.0.0',
            personalApiKey: '<ph_personal_api_key>'
        }
    }
})
```
